## (a) Mechanism hypothesis

On **interior→exterior exit**, the ~4 m Y step is a **same-frame, two-phase handoff inside shared simulation**, not a renderer fork:

1. **Alter phase (controller move):** horizontal `setPosition_w` triggers portal detection; `setParentCell(world)` **reparents first** and **preserves interior world-Y (~5.1)** via `detachFromObject(DF_world)` writing the full world transform into `m_objectToParent`.
2. **Post-alter collision pass:** with `parentCell == world` but object Y still ~5.1, `Footprint::updateHeights` samples **terrain (~1.06)**; the **`snapObjectToGround` loop** (not `snapToGround`) then writes that terrain Y onto the **object** via `setObjectPosition_p`.

That produces a **one-frame discontinuity vs the prior frame** (interior ~5.1 → exterior ~1.06). `Footprint::snapToGround` only updates footprint `m_position_p`; the visible object-Y pop is **`snapObjectToGround` → `setObjectPosition_p`**.

A **second mechanism** (wall-graze only, not every-exit per locked #4) is `resolveCollisions` `resetPos = transformToCell(foyer1, lastPos, world)` reintroducing pre-crossing interior height — opposite direction (terrain → interior floor).

**Renderer note:** No `#ifdef` D3D9/D3D11 branch exists on this Y path. A plausible **presentation amplifier** (not contradicting shared `Camera::applyState`): `FreeChaseCamera::alter` runs **before** post-alter `CollisionWorld::update`, so the camera can capture target at Y~5.1 while the player object is dropped to Y~1.06 later the same frame — a camera/object vertical desync at draw time, modulated cross-frame by `elapsedTime`/`Clock::frameTime()` (timestep), not by different view-matrix push code.

---

## (b) File:line evidence — field ownership and ordering

### Which field holds Y at each step (exit frame)

| Step | Parent cell | Object Y authority | Footprint Y authority |
|------|-------------|-------------------|----------------------|
| End of prior frame | `foyer1` | `m_objectToParent` (cell-local ~0.1) → `getTransform_o2w()` ≈ **5.1** | `m_position_p` (cell-local floor); `m_position_w` cached |
| Controller move | `foyer1` → **`world`** | `setPosition_w` / portal reframe | unchanged until collision |
| After `setParentCell(world)` | **`world`** | **`m_objectToParent` = world transform, Y still ≈ 5.1** (`detachFromObject`) | `Footprint::cellChanged` (client): floor attach only, **no Y write** |
| After `updatePostResolve` | `world` | object Y still ≈ 5.1 | `snapToGround` sets **`m_position_p.y = m_groundHeight`** only |
| After `snapObjectToGround` loop | `world` | **`getOwner()->setPosition_p` → world Y ≈ 1.06** | footprint already at ground height |

### Phase 1 — Portal reparent (preserves interior world-Y)

Portal detection uses world segment; crossing calls `setParentCell`:

```129:204:src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/portal/CellProperty.cpp
	Vector start = object.getTransform_p2w().rotateTranslate_l2p(oldPosition_p);
	Vector end   = object.getPosition_w();
	// ...
		object.setParentCell(targetCell);
```

`setParentCell` on exit to world:

```1399:1408:src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.cpp
	if (!isInWorldCell())
		detachFromObject(DF_world);
	if (cellProperty != CellProperty::getWorldCellProperty())
		attachToObject_w(&cellProperty->getOwner(), false);
	cellChanged(false);
```

`detachFromObject(DF_world)` preserves world pose in parent transform (Y unchanged):

```1996:2005:src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.cpp
	m_objectToParent = shouldAttach ? getTransform_o2c() : getTransform_o2w();
	deleteLocalTransform(m_objectToWorld);
	m_objectToWorld = NULL;
```

World cell, unattached: `getTransform_o2w()` **is** `m_objectToParent`; world position comes from that:

```1418:1445:src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.cpp
	if (m_attachedToObject)
	{
		m_objectToWorld->multiply(m_attachedToObject->getTransform_o2w(), m_objectToParent);
		return *m_objectToWorld;
	}
	return m_objectToParent;
```

```691:694:src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/Object.h
inline const Vector Object::getPosition_w() const
{
	return getTransform_o2w().getPosition_p();
}
```

